1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,650
AI agents can write code. Long-running work fails when context, risk, and validation are reset every session.

2
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:13,650
Agent HQ OS treats context as runtime state, not chat history.

3
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:22,649
Tasks move through visible queue and state transitions before they are treated as complete.

4
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:32,649
Publishing, credentials, infrastructure, messaging, and trading-adjacent work stop at explicit human gates.

5
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:43,649
Validation comes before confidence. Claims are not done until local evidence exists.

6
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:54,649
Retries are allowed only when the failure is actually retryable.

7
00:00:55,000 --> 00:01:04,650
Telemetry turns the result of one session into safer starting context for the next.

8
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:14,650
This is not autopilot. It is safe bounded autonomy with human review where it matters. Agent HQ OS is a public scaffold for practical AI runtime operations.
